choices.text:
I am not a prime number.
I am between 20 and 40.
I am one more than a square number.
What number am I?
You are the sum of two consecutive primes, which means you are either 31 or 59. However, neither of these numbers is between 20 and 40, so they cannot be your answer. Therefore, there may not be a unique number that satisfies all three clues.
